You are prompted for an answer. If I wanted to be prompted for
an answer in this deck, I would have specified it in the card model.

I know that this behavior is intended, but it's anoying. I review three decks every
day and I have to switch this preference if I change the deck. I have also a deck where
for some cards I have an answer specified and for other cards not.

This patch fixes the error. (The info text in preferences needs to be changed too)

diff --git a/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java b/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
index c0d241d..29e18e1 100644
--- a/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
+++ b/src/com/ichi2/anki/Card.java
@@ -1078,8 +1078,8 @@
        String typeAnswer = myCardModel.getTypeAnswer();
