Originally reported on Google Code with ID 1796 I have a mobile device that's non-standard, I can't find its firmware, no root app works. Without root, I can't install the IPA fonts into system. The Phonetic symbols are all displayed as white bricks.
Then I noticed this reply on stackoverflow : http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10051915/how-to-install-custom-font-in-android-device
-------- See here @CommonsWare answer, You cannot add fonts to an existing device, except as part of a custom firmware build, or possibly by rooting the device.
but you can add fonts in your appliction. like:
TextView txtvw=(TextView)findViewById(R.id.textviewname);
Typeface typface=Typeface.createFromAsset(getAssets(),"fonts/burmese.ttf");
txtvw.setTypeface(typface);
Note: put your font in assets/fonts dir in project --------
Could you implement this feature. to allow customized font in a non-system location? It would be nice to have this ability on devices without root.
